; ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
; SDNA PULSE — Billion Barrier Verification
; ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
; Implements the SDNA density check from Genlex Spec:
;   If data density < 0.999999999, reject the manifestation.
;
; This program:
;   1. Loads a test value
;   2. Modulates it through the heartbeat
;   3. Computes resonance density
;   4. Checks against the Billion Barrier
;   5. Outputs PASS (1.0) or FAIL (0.0)
; ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

; Load test value and anchor
LOAD_IMM r0 #1.0              ; test signal: 1.0
LOAD_IMM r1 #ANCHOR           ; heartbeat

; Modulate through 5 pulse cycles
PULSE r0 0 0                  ; r0 *= 1.092777...
PULSE r0 0 0                  ; r0 *= 1.092777...
PULSE r0 0 0                  ; r0 *= 1.092777...
PULSE r0 0 0                  ; r0 *= 1.092777...
PULSE r0 0 0                  ; r0 = 1.0 * ANCHOR^5

; Compute density: |r0| * ANCHOR
DENSITY r0 0 0                ; r0 = |r0| * ANCHOR

; Load the Billion Barrier
LOAD_IMM r2 #BILLION          ; r2 = 0.999999999

; Compare: did we pass the barrier?
CMP_GT r0 r2 0                ; r0 = (density > barrier) ? 1.0 : 0.0

; Store result
STORE_OUT r0 0 0              ; output: 1.0 = PASS, 0.0 = FAIL

HALT
